<A>__{mack drops his pants and sits on the throne. he reaches over and turns on the radio resting on the wash basin. a farm report comes on just as...}
<L>__{interior living room day}
<A>__{a needle drops on a 78, filling the room with the scratchy sounds of a coonass waltz. butch's eyes come to life.}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{you dance, lottie?}
<C>__{lottie}
<D>__{lawd goodness no.}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{here, jus' follow me.}
<A>__{he takes her in his arms and slowly but surely adjusts her movement to his. after a few rough turns they're not too bad. phillip can't help but smile as he and cleve watch and giggle. butch and lottie dance, swirling around the room.}
<C>__{lottie}
<D>__{mr. poe, you sure can move.}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{oughta be able to. was raised in a dime a dance whorehouse.}
<C>__{lottie}
<D>__{yer' foolin' me?}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{no, ma'am. my mama would dance their asses out of the fryin' pan and into the back room fire.}
<A>__{butch spots phillip and cleve, watching, giggling.}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{get on yer' feet, buzz. you'n cleve shake a leg.}
<C>__{lottie}
<P>__{(encouraging)}
<D>__{well go on!}
<A>__{cleve and phillip reluctantly stand and stare at one another.}
<C>__{butch}
<D>__{dance, boys!}
<A>__{the little boys do their best to emulate the adults and soon they're laughing and dancing, too. the record stops. they all clap and laugh. butch hears something... the radio in the bathroom.}
